# Build order (do not skip phases)

Work `docs/TASKS.md` top to bottom. The gates below are hard stops.

- **Phase 0 — Runnable skeleton.** Backend boots, `pytest` passes (synthetic proof in
  `test_geometry.py` already demonstrates the core mechanism). Frontend renders a pair and posts
  a choice.
- **Phase 1 — Validation (the whole point).** Real elicitation loop end-to-end; fit a single
  shared vector; the three falsifiable tests run and report.
  **GATE:** hold-out accuracy must beat chance on real user data. If it does not, STOP and
  surface the result — the premise has failed and later phases are unjustified.
- **Phase 2 — Hierarchy + articulation.** Shared `g` + per-domain offsets; axis discovery +
  labeling; the confirmation step where the AI names axes and the user ratifies.
  **GATE:** cross-domain transfer must beat chance, or downgrade to per-domain assessments.
- **Phase 3 — Color-affect module.** Personalized color→emotion elicitation and map.
- **Phase 4 — Generation.** Compose a brief from the kernel and route to a generator per domain.
  This is expensive; do not start it until Phases 1–2 gates pass.

When unsure whether to build something, check which phase it belongs to. Never pull Phase 4 work
forward to "make it feel real" — a validated kernel is what makes it real.
